  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nSuppose you have a Truffle project that uses `truffle.js` instead of `truffle-config.js`.\r\n\r\nWhen you attempt to have Truffle do anything, Truffle will:\r\n1. Warn you that you have both `truffle.js` and `truffle-config.js`, even though you don't;\r\n2. Use the default configuration residing in this imaginary `truffle-config.js`, rather than the one you specified in `truffle.js`\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create a new directory and run `truffle init`\r\n2. Rename `truffle-config.js` to `truffle.js`\r\n3. In `truffle.js`, uncomment the `version` line, and change the version to `\"0.7.0\"`\r\n4. Run `truffle version`\r\n5. Observe the warning that was printed out\r\n6. Observe that the solc version printed out was 0.5.16 instead of 0.7.0\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nWhen `truffle-config.js` is not present, Truffle should use the settings in `truffle.js`, and should not warn about the former being present when it's not.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nSee above.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Release Linux Mint 20 Ulyana 64-bit\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.1.41\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 10.15.3\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.14.5",
